Sacvin Nigeria Limited, a plastics manufacturing company, says it has received three ISO certifications from G-CERTI Company Limited. According to company, the certifications are ISO 9001: 2015; ISO 14001: 2015 and ISO 45001: 2018. It noted that the International Organization for Standardization develops worldwide technical, industrial and commercial standards for international best practices and consistency. “The ISO 9001: 2015 and ISO 14001:2015 cover management systems and environmental management systems respectively while ISO 45001: 2018 covers occupational health and safety management systems,” the company said in a statement. It said the certifications attested to it meeting international standards in quality, environmental impact, and occupational health and safety. According to the statement, the company has four operational factories in Kano and Lagos, and has a fifth factory coming on stream soon.